Personally speaking, the best way to take user interface guidance from
iTunes is to treat it as a vast tome of what not to do. It doesn't follow
Apple's own guidelines, it's ugly, and it behaves strangely in many ways.
The traffic light button on a window should be treated as sacred: they act
exactly the same way in every single app you ever encounter. Completely
altering the function of one of them just to add some new UI mode is
ridiculous; what if I want to actually, say, make my iTunes window be as
large as possible? If I click the button explicitly designed for that,
only confusion results.

--
Michael Ash
Rogue Amoeba Software
